# Feedback & Medical Reports Feature Walkthrough

I have successfully implemented both requested features. The new changes enhance the patient experience and grant the admin more control over the system.

## 1. Doctor Feedback & Ratings System
*   **Database Models:** Created `feedbackModel.js` to store feedback.
*   **Patient Experience (`MyAppointments.jsx`):** 
    *   Patients now see a "Leave Feedback" button for completed appointments.
    *   Clicking it opens a modal allowing them to leave a 1-5 star rating and write a short review.
*   **Doctor Profile (`Appointments.jsx`):**
    *   When a patient is booking an appointment, they can see the Doctor's **Average Rating** (e.g. 4.5 / 5) based on all their feedbacks.
    *   Up to 3 of the most recent patient reviews are displayed below the "About" section.
*   **Admin Control (`Feedbacks.jsx`):**
    *   A new "Feedbacks" navigation item was added to the Admin panel sidebar.
    *   Admins can view all patient feedback across the platform and delete any inappropriate ones.

## 2. Medical Reports Module
*   **Database Models:** Created `reportModel.js` to store document metadata and the Cloudinary URL.
*   **Patient Experience (`Navbar.jsx` & `MyReports.jsx`):**
    *   The confusing "Admin/Doctor Login" button on the patient frontend was removed.
    *   It was replaced with a **My Reports** page. Patients can securely upload (`.pdf`, `.jpg`, `.png`, etc.) medical documents like prescriptions or X-ray reports.
    *   They can view/download or delete their own reports anytime.
*   **Admin Control (`PatientReports.jsx`):**
    *   A new "Patient Reports" navigation item was added to the Admin panel sidebar.
    *   Admins can view all registered patients and click "Manage Reports" to view their uploaded files.
    *   Admins also have the power to upload new reports on behalf of the patient or delete existing ones.

> [!TIP]
> Make sure both frontend (`localhost:5173`) and admin (`localhost:5174`) servers are running to view these changes. The backend server might need a restart if you haven't restarted it after the file creations.

**Note on `.dcm` files:** As requested, I have ensured Cloudinary uses `resource_type: "auto"`, which will work for standard files. We skipped focusing on very large `.dcm` uploads for now to avoid hitting the free tier limits of Cloudinary.
